Steps to Reproduce:

1. Run your cocos2d-x app on android
2. Switch to another activity outside the app
3.  applicationDidEnterBackground is not called

Notes:
I found some fixed issues regarding this problem back in 2011 #462 #238 [android]. In Cocos2dxGLSurfaceView.java:
```java
@Override
public void onPause() {
this.queueEvent(new Runnable() {
@Override
public void run() {
Cocos2dxGLSurfaceView.this.mCocos2dxRenderer.handleOnPause();
}
});
this.setRenderMode(RENDERMODE_WHEN_DIRTY);
//super.onPause();
}
```
I was thinking to fix it by uncommmenting the last line super.onPause() but that didn't work unfortunately, the code is different than the change of 2011, it had the super.onPause().

- cocos2d-x version: 3.14 (but possibly in all previous releases where this code exists)
- devices test on: N/A
